This paper deals with privacy-preserving data collection and estimation, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a novel decoding algorithm and methodology for estimating joint distributions, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The use of data dictionaries and the estimation of relationships between multiple variables suggest that this paper could also be categorized under databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the privacy-preserving aspect of the data collection and estimation could also place this paper under social and information networks (cs.SI).
